    DirectLGraph is a mutable representation of a directed labeled multigraph. This graph contains unique nodes connected by one-way edges. There can be any number of edges between each pair of nodes (zero, one, or more). Each edge has a non-unique label. No two edges with the same parent and child nodes will have the same edge label, and no two nodes store equal data.
